strtools.py
Go to the documentation of this file.
1 #!/usr/bin/env python3
2 # -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
3 # vim:fileencoding=utf-8
4 """
5 @file strtools.py
6 @package pybooster.strtools
7 @author Devyn Collier Johnson <DevynCJohnson@Gmail.com>
8 @copyright LGPLv3
9 @brief Functions for various string and character manipulations
10 @version 2016.03.18
11 
12 @section DESCRIPTION
13 This library contains\n
14  - Constants for various characters and character ranges\n
15  - Functions for various string and character manipulations\n
16  - Ascii, Hex (\\x*), UTF-8 (\\u*), UTF-16BE/UTF-32 (\\U*), HTML-Entities (&#*;)\n
17 
18 C-escapes = JS-escapes = HTML-named-ref = decimal ncr = hex ncr\n
19 '\\U0001d4c3' = '\\ud835\\udcc3' = &nscr; = &#120003; = &#x1D4C3;\n
20 '\\U0001d4a9' = '\\ud835\\udca9' = &Nscr; = &#119977; = &#x1D4A9;\n
21 
22 unicode+hex = 0x notation = css = utf16 = utf8 = uri%\n
23 U+1D4C3 = 0x1D4C3 = \01D4C3 = D835 DCC3 = F0 9D 93 83 = %F0%9D%93%83\n
24 U+1D4A9 = 0x1D4A9 = \01D4A9 = D835 DCA9 = F0 9D 92 A9 = %F0%9D%92%A9\n
25 
26 @section VARIABLES
27  - _refnum: stores an HTML reference number as a string (&#38;)\n
28  - _refname: stores an HTML name entity as a string (&amp;)\n
29  - _name: stores an unicode character name\n
30  - _char: stores a single character or an escape sequence (\\x26)\n
31  - _str: stores a string/text\n
32  - _int: stores an integer\n
33  - _hex: stores a hex sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence\n
34  - _oct: stores an octal sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence\n
35  - _bin: stores a binary sequence as an integer, str, or escape sequence\n
36  - _bytes: stores a bytes-type object\n
37  - _dict: specify a dictionary\n
38  - _search: a value to find\n
39  - _assert: indicate that some condition be met\n
40  - _numbase: specify the base of the number ('2'=binary; '16'=hex; etc.)\n
41  - _escape: boolean; "True" (the default) makes a function escape the output\n
42  - _endian: specify endian (little/big); default is the native value\n
43  - _encoding: specify encoding; the default value is "utf8"\n
44 
45 @section LICENSE
46 GNU Lesser General Public License v3
47 Copyright (c) Devyn Collier Johnson, All rights reserved.

56 MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. See the GNU
57 Lesser General Public License for more details.
58 
59 You should have received a copy of the GNU Lesser General Public
60 License along with this library.
61 """

366 INCOMPLETE_REF = re.compile('&[#]?[0-9A-Za-z]+')
367 ENTITY_REF = re.compile('&[0-9A-Za-z]+;')
368 CHAR_REF = re.compile('&#(?:[0-9]+|[Xx][0-9A-Fa-f]+);')
369 CHAR_REF2 = re.compile(
370  r'&(#[0-9]+;?'
371  r'|#[xX][0-9a-fA-F]+;?'
372  r'|[^\t\n\f <&#;]{1,32};?)'
373 )
374 LEADING_SURROGATE = re.compile(r'[\ud800-\udbff]')
375 TRAILING_SURROGATE = re.compile(r'[\udc00-\udfff]')

536 """
537 The values in CODES includes the HTML entity names and numbers
538 The characters used as keys are encoded in UTF8 (\\u) or UTF-16BE (\\U)
539 
540 HTML5_REF maps the names of HTML5 character references to characters.
541 
542 NAME2INT maps character names to hexadecimal integers.
543 
544 INVALID_CHARREFS maps hexadecimal integers to characters that should not be used in HTML5
545 """

5424 def splitsentencesstr(_str_of_sentences: str) -> list:
5425  """Split a string by sentence"""
5426  _array = re.split(r'[\.\?!;]*', _str_of_sentences)
5427  inputarray = []
5428  for i in _array:
5429  i = i.strip()
5430  if len(i):
5431  inputarray.append(i)
5432  return inputarray

5435 def sqlstr(_obj, _strength: int=0) -> str:
5436  """Convert an object to a string and format the string
5437  to protect against SQL-Injection Attacks
5438  _strength indicates what characters should be removed or escaped
5439  0 = (Default) Remove curly quotes, commas, and brackets; escape quotes, slashes, and dashes
5440  1 = Same as 0, but removes characters instead of escaping
5441  2 = Same as 1, but remove additional characters such as .?!#;&%^:
5442  3 = Only keep ASCII letters and space
5443  """
5444  _obj = str(_obj)
5445  if _strength >= 3: # Only keep ASCII letters and space
5446  _out = r''
5447  for i in _obj:
5448  if i.isalpha() or i is r' ':
5449  _out += i
5450  return _out
5451  _obj = _obj.replace(r'{', r'').replace(r'}', r'').replace('\\', r'')
5452  _obj = _obj.replace(r'', r'').replace(r'', r'').replace(r'', r'').replace(r'', r'').replace(r'', r'').replace(r'', r'') # Curly Quotes and Commas
5453  if not _strength: # _strength == 0
5454  return _obj.replace(r'"', r'&quot;').replace('\'', r'&#39;').replace(r'`', r'&#96;').replace(r'--', r'-')
5455  else: # _strength >= 1
5456  _obj = _obj.replace(r'"', r'').replace('\'', r'').replace(r'`', r'').replace(r'-', r'')
5457  if _strength >= 2:
5458  return _obj.replace(r'%', r'').replace(r'^', r'').replace(r':', r'').replace(r'#', r'').replace(r';', r'').replace(r'&', r'').replace(r'.', r'').replace(r'?', r'').replace(r'!', r'')
5459  return _obj

5470 def fval(_dict: dict, _search) -> str:
5471  """Search a dictionary by value and stop on first instance
5472  This searches key values that are tuples, lists, or strings
5473  Returns the key (if found); else returns empty string
5474  """
5475  for key, val in _dict.items():
5476  if isinstance(val, str) and val == _search:
5477  return key
5478  elif _search in val:
5479  return key
5480  return ''
5481 
5482 
5483 def fvalhtml(_search: str, _type: str) -> str:
5484  """Search a dict by value to find the paired value
5485  Stop on first instance
5486  For example, this finds '&#38;' or '&amp;' and returns the other value
5487  Returns HTML entity if found; else return empty string
5488  """
5489  _tuples = CODES.values()
5490  for v in _tuples:
5491  if not isinstance(v, (tuple, list)) or _search not in v:
5492  continue
5493  elif len(v) < 2 or len(v) > 4:
5494  continue
5495  if v[0] != _search:
5496  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[0]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[0]):
5497  return v[0]
5498  elif v[1] != _search:
5499  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[1]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[1]):
5500  return v[1]
5501  elif len(v) is 3 and v[2] != _search:
5502  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[2]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[2]):
5503  return v[2]
5504  elif len(v) is 4 and v[3] != _search:
5505  if (_type is 'name' and '#' not in v[3]) or (_type is 'num' and '&#' in v[3]):
5506  return v[3]
5507  return ''

5509 
5510 def noescape(_hex: str) -> str:
5511  """Remove escapes from a single character hex string
5512  (\\U00000026, \\u0026, \\x26)
5513  """
5514  if '\\U' in _hex and len(_hex) is 10:
5515  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\U', ''), 16)
5516  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')
5517  return eval('"\\U{0}"'.format(_hex[:].zfill(8)))
5518  elif '\\u' in _hex and len(_hex) is 6:
5519  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\u', ''), 16)
5520  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')
5521  return eval('"\\u{0}"'.format(_hex[:].zfill(4)))
5522  elif '\\x' in _hex and (len(_hex) % 4) is 0:
5523  _utf8_strict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
5524  if _hex.count('\\x') is 4:
5525  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5526  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\\x{0[3]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5527  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5528  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 3:
5529  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5530  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5531  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5532  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 2:
5533  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
5534  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\'' + _utf8_strict
5535  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
5536  elif _hex.count('\\x') is 1:
5537  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\x', ''), 16)
5538  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')[:].zfill(2)
5539  return eval('\'\\x{0}\''.format(_hex))
5540  else:
5541  raise Exception('Invalid input passed to noescape()!')
5542  elif isinstance(_hex, str) and len(_hex) is 1:
5543  return _hex
5544  else:
5545  raise Exception('Invalid input passed to noescape()!')
5546

5550 
5551 def isascii(_str: str) -> bool:
5552  """Test if a character is within the Ascii limit
5553  >>> isascii('B')
5554  True
5555  >>> isascii('b')
5556  True
5557  >>> isascii('1')
5558  True
5559  >>> isascii('')
5560  False
5561  >>> isascii('')
5562  False
5563  >>> isascii('')
5564  False
5565  """
5566  try:
5567  return 0 <= ord(_str) < UPPER_LIMIT_ASCII_EXT
5568  except SyntaxError:
5569  return False
5570 
5571 
5572 def isstrascii(_str: str) -> bool:
5573  """Test if a string is within the Ascii limit
5574  >>> isstrascii('B')
5575  True
5576  >>> isstrascii('b')
5577  True
5578  >>> isstrascii('123')
5579  True
5580  >>> isstrascii('qwerty')
5581  True
5582  >>> isstrascii('')
5583  False
5584  >>> isstrascii('')
5585  False
5586  >>> isstrascii('123qwerty')
5587  False
5588  """
5589  return all(False for x in _str if not isascii(x))
5590 
5591 
5592 def isctrlascii(_str: str) -> bool:
5593  """Test if a character is within the Control Ascii limit
5594  >>> isctrlascii('\\r')
5595  True
5596  >>> isctrlascii('\\n')
5597  True
5598  >>> isctrlascii('\\a')
5599  True
5600  >>> isctrlascii('\\0')
5601  True
5602  >>> isctrlascii('')
5603  False
5604  >>> isctrlascii('')
5605  False
5606  """
5607  try:
5608  return LOWER_LIMIT_ASCII_CTRL <= ord(_str) <= UPPER_LIMIT_ASCII_CTRL
5609  except SyntaxError:

5808 def isunicode(_str: str) -> bool: # flake8: noqa
5809  """Test if a string is within the Unicode limit"""
5810  assert isinstance(_str, (str, bytes)), \
5811  'An invalid datatype was passed to isunicode()!'
5812  _utfstrict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
5813  _fmt = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utfstrict
5814  if len(_str) is 10 and '\\U' in _str:
5815  _int = int(_str.replace('\\U', ''), 16)
5816  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5817  elif len(_str) is 6 and '\\u' in _str:
5818  _int = int(_str.replace('\\u', ''), 16)
5819  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5820  elif _str.count('\\x') is 1 and (len(_str) % 4) is 0:
5821  _int = int(_str.replace('\\x', '0x'), 16)
5822  return _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE
5823  elif _str.count('\\x') >= 2 and (len(_str) % 4) is 0:
5824  try:
5825  eval(_fmt.format(_str.split('\\x')[1:]))
5826  except SyntaxError:
5827  return False
5828  return True
5829  elif isinstance(_str, bytes):
5830  try:
5831  _str.decode('utf8', 'strict')
5832  except SyntaxError:
5833  return False
5834  return True
5835  elif len(_str) is 1:
5836  try:
5837  if len(_str.encode('utf-16', 'strict')):
5838  return True
5839  except SyntaxError:
5840  return False
5841  return False

5956  r"""Shrink a 16-bit hex escape to a 8-bit hex escape

6075 def htmlescape(_str: str, quote: bool=True):
6076  """Replace special characters "&", "<", and ">" to HTML-escapes
6077  If the optional flag quote is true (default), double quote (") and
6078  single quote (') characters are also escaped.
6079  >>> htmlescape('This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).')
6080  'This &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a &quot;test&quot; (&amp;).'
6081  >>> htmlescape('This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).', False)
6082  'This &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a "test" (&amp;).'
6083  """
6084  _str = _str.replace('&', '&amp;').replace('<', '&lt;').replace('>', '&gt;')
6085  if quote:
6086  _str = _str.replace('"', '&quot;').replace('\'', '&#39;')
6087  return _str

6090 def htmlunescape(_str: str):
6091  """Unescape &, ', ", <, and >
6092  >>> htmlunescape('This &#x3c;b&#62;is&lt;/b&gt; a &#34;test&quot; (&amp;).')
6093  'This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).'
6094  >>> htmlunescape('This &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; a &quot;test&quot; (&amp;).')
6095  'This <b>is</b> a "test" (&).'
6096  """
6097  if '&' not in _str:
6098  return _str
6099  _str = _str.replace('&#x27;', r'\'').replace('&#39;', r'\'').replace('&apos;', r'\'')
6100  _str = _str.replace('&#x22;', '"').replace('&#34;', '"').replace('&quot;', '"')
6101  _str = _str.replace('&#x3c;', '<').replace('&#60;', '<').replace('&lt;', '<')
6102  _str = _str.replace('&#x3e;', '>').replace('&#62;', '>').replace('&gt;', '>')
6103  _str = _str.replace('&x26;', '&').replace('&#38;', '&').replace('&amp;', '&')

6107 def noescutf8hex(_hex: str) -> str:
6108  r"""Remove escapes from UTF-8 hex strings (\\x26)
6109  >>> noescutf8hex('\\x26')
6110  '&'
6111  """
6112  if '\\x' in _hex and (len(_hex) % 4) is 0:
6113  _utf8_strict = '.decode(\'utf8\', \'strict\')'
6114  if _hex.count('\\') == 3:
6115  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6116  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6117  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6118  elif _hex.count('\\') == 2:
6119  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6120  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6121  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6122  elif _hex.count('\\') == 4:
6123  _hex = _hex.split('\\x')[1:]
6124  _eval_str = 'b\'\\x{0[0]}\\x{0[1]}\\x{0[2]}\\x{0[3]}\'' + _utf8_strict
6125  return eval(_eval_str.format(_hex))
6126  elif _hex.count('\\') == 1:
6127  _int = int(_hex.replace('\\x', ''), 16)
6128  _hex = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')[:].zfill(2)
6129  return eval('\'\\x{0}\''.format(_hex))
6130  if isinstance(_hex, str) and len(_hex) is 1:
6131  return _hex
6132  raise ValueError('Invalid input passed to noescutf8hex()!')

6173 def int2char(_int, _numbase: str='10', _escape: bool=True) -> str:
6174  """Convert an integer (as a str or int type) to a character
6175  The integer may be decimal, hex, octal, or binary
6176  By default, the returned value is escaped unicode (\\U0000000)
6177  int2char(_int, _numbase, _escape) => str
6178  _int - number to convert to a character
6179  _numbase - Specify the int's base (2, 8, 10, 16)
6180  _escape - False = No escapes; True = Escapes
6181  int2char(38) => \\U00000026
6182  int2char('38') => \\U00000026
6183  int2char('0x26') => \\U00000026
6184  int2char(0x26) => \\U00000026
6185  int2char('26', '16') => \\U00000026
6186  int2char('26', '16', False) => &
6187  """
6188  if isinstance(_int, str):
6189  if '0x' in _int or _numbase is '16' or _numbase is 'hex':
6190  _int = int(_int, 16)
6191  elif '0b' in _int or _numbase is '2' or _numbase is 'bin':
6192  _int = int(_int, 2)
6193  elif '0o' in _int or _numbase is '8' or _numbase is 'oct':
6194  _int = int(_int, 8)
6195  else:
6196  _int = int(_int, 10)
6197  if isinstance(_int, int):
6198  if _escape:
6199  _int = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')[:].zfill(8)
6200  return '\\U{0}'.format(_int)
6201  else:
6202  if LOWER_LIMIT_ASCII_CTRL <= _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UTF8:
6203  return chr(_int)
6204  elif UPPER_LIMIT_UTF8 < _int <= UPPER_LIMIT_UNICODE:
6205  _int = hex(_int).replace('0x', '')
6206  return eval('"\\U{0}"'.format(_int[:].zfill(8)))
6207  raise ValueError(
6208  'An out-of-range integer passed to int2char()!'
6209  )
6210  raise TypeError('Invalid datatype passed to int2char()!')
6211 
6212 
6213 def hexstr2char(_hex: str, _escape: bool=True) -> str:
6214  """Convert a hex number (as a string) to a character
6215  hexstr2char('0x26') => \\U00000026
6216  hexstr2char(0x26) => \\U00000026
6217  hexstr2char('26', False) => &
6218  """
6219  return int2char(_hex, '16', _escape)
6220

6222 def hexint2char(_hex: int, _escape: bool=True) -> str:
6223  """Convert a hex integer to a character
6224  hexint2char(0x26) => \\U00000026
6225  hexint2char(0x26, False) => &
6226  """
6227  return int2char(_hex, '16', _escape)

6397 def hex2unicodehex(_hex: str or int) -> str:
6398  """Convert hexadecimal to Unicode+Hex Notation"""
6399  if isinstance(_hex, str):
6400  if '0x' in _hex:
6401  _hex = _hex.replace('0x', '')
6402  if '\\x' in _hex:
6403  _hex = _hex.replace('\\x', '')
6404  if '\\U' in _hex:
6405  _hex = _hex.replace('\\U000', '').replace('\\U00', '')
6406  _hex = _hex.replace('\\U0', '').replace('\\U', '')
6407  if '\\u' in _hex:
6408  _hex = _hex.replace('\\u00', '').replace('\\u0', '')
6409  _hex = _hex.replace('\\u', '')
6410  if '\\0' in _hex:
6411  _hex = _hex.replace('\\0', '')
6412  if '&#x' in _hex:
6413  _hex = _hex.replace('&#x', '').replace(';', '')
6414  return 'U+{0}'.format(_hex)
6415  elif isinstance(_hex, int):
6416  _hex = hex(_hex).replace('0x', '')
6417  return 'U+{0}'.format(_hex)
6418  raise TypeError('Invalid datatype passed to hex2unicodehex()!')
